==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slog
<hw>Slog</hw> <pr>(sl⟦ocr⟧g)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Slug</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To hit hard, esp. with
little attention to aim or the like, as in cricket or boxing; to
slug.</def> <mark>[Cant or Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slog</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slog
<hw>Slog</hw> <pr>(sl⟦ocr⟧g)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>to
walk heavily; to plod; to walk through resisting terrain, as in
mud.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To work steadily and ploddingly; to toil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slogger</ent>⟦br⟧
